  "texts": [
    "Namely, F t is obtained from the previ- ous approximation F t-1 in an additive manner: F t = F t-1 + αh t, where α is a step size and h t: R m → R (a base predictor) is chosen from a family of functions H in order to minimize the expected loss:",
    "For the training of our CatBoost model, we used the Multivariate RMSE as loss function:",
    "where N is the number of data points, y(i) is the i-th measurement, and ŷ(i) is its corresponding prediction, made with network weights θ.",
    "Ms are a set of supervised learning methods used for regression and classification, first developed by Vapnik et al.",
    "When SVM is applied to a regression problem, it is denominated Support Vector Regression (SVR)."
  ]
}